# React Component Patterns

## Component Organization

- **Shared**: `src/components/` — reusable across features (435+ files)
- **Feature-scoped**: co-located in `src/app/.../components/` next to their page
- Each component: own directory with `index.tsx` + optional `.module.scss`
- Never put feature-specific components in `src/components/`

## UI Library — Mantine v7

- All UI primitives from `@mantine/core` — do NOT use raw HTML equivalents when Mantine has a component
- Modals: `@mantine/modals` via `ModalsProvider` — use `modals.open()` or `modals.openConfirmModal()`
- Notifications: custom wrapper only — always use `showToast()` from `@/components/toast`

```typescript
import { showToast } from '@/components/toast';
showToast({ type: 'success', title: 'Saved', message: 'Changes applied' });
showToast({ type: 'error', title: 'Failed', message: error.message });
```

## Forms — Mantine Form + Custom Validation

```typescript
import { useForm } from '@mantine/form';
const form = useForm({
  mode: 'uncontrolled',
  initialValues: { email: '', password: '' },
  validate: { email: (v) => (!v ? t('required') : null) },
});
```

- Custom validation hook: `@/hooks/useFormValidation` — supports `required()`, `email()`, `minLength()`, `pattern()`, `custom()`
- Validation messages MUST use `useTranslations()` — never hardcoded English

## Custom Hooks (`src/hooks/`)

| Hook | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `useFormValidation` | Declarative form validation rules |
| `useEmployeeSearch` | RTK Query mutation + pagination |
| `useAttendanceTabPersistence` | Tab state in localStorage |
| `useFetchLatestSchedule` | Schedule polling |
| `useFetchUnreadNotifications` | Notification count |
| `usePhysicsDrag` | Physics-based drag with RAF cleanup |
| `useLoginForm`, `useMFAForm`, etc. | Feature-specific form logic |

## Performance Rules — Optimize Only When Needed

**useMemo** — use when there is a **measurable reason**:
- TanStack Table column definitions (complex object creation)
- Filtered/transformed lists over large datasets from API
- Expensive computations (sorting, grouping, heavy transformations)

**useMemo — do NOT use when:**
- The expression is trivial: `x ?? {}`, `Boolean(x)`, `String(x)`, simple casts
- It's a simple string concatenation or boolean check
- Memoization adds more complexity than the value it provides
- There is no measurable render/performance benefit

```typescript
// BAD: useMemo on trivial expressions — adds noise, zero perf gain
const label = useMemo(() => `${firstName} ${lastName}`, [firstName, lastName]);
const isValid = useMemo(() => !!email, [email]);
const fallback = useMemo(() => value ?? {}, [value]);

// GOOD: just compute inline — these are O(1) operations
const label = `${firstName} ${lastName}`;
const isValid = !!email;
const fallback = value ?? {};

// GOOD: useMemo where it actually matters
const sortedRows = useMemo(() => rows.sort((a, b) => a.date - b.date), [rows]);
const columns = useMemo(() => buildColumnDefs(t, role, isEditable), [t, role, isEditable]);
```

**useCallback** — use when:
- Passing handlers as props to `React.memo` children
- Passing handlers to `useEffect` dependency arrays
- WebSocket event handlers

**React.memo** — required for:
- Row components inside `.map()` for lists > 20 items
- Table cell renderers in TanStack Table
- Existing examples: `FilterItem`, `FilterOptions`, `EmployeeRow`, `NameCell`

**next/dynamic** — required for:
- Modals, drawers, and dialogs not visible on initial render
- Chart components (Recharts)
- Heavy form components loaded conditionally

```typescript
const DynamicModal = dynamic(() => import('./HeavyModal'));
const DynamicChart = dynamic(() => import('./Chart'), { ssr: false });
```

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

```typescript
// NEVER: empty useEffect
useEffect(() => {}, [options]); // Found in FilterItem.tsx — this is a no-op

// NEVER: missing cleanup for timers/subscriptions
useEffect(() => {
  const id = setInterval(fn, 1000);
  // Missing: return () => clearInterval(id);
}, []);

// NEVER: inline objects in memoized child props
<MemoizedChild style={{ color: 'red' }} /> // Creates new ref every render

// NEVER: business logic in JSX return
return <div>{data.filter(x => x.active).map(x => <Row key={x.id} {...transform(x)} />)}</div>;
// Extract: const activeRows = useMemo(() => data.filter(...).map(...), [data]);
```

## SSR Safety

Any component accessing browser APIs must guard:

```typescript
// Use storageManager — NOT direct localStorage/sessionStorage
import { getLocalStorage, setLocalStorage } from '@/utils/storageManager';

// For other browser APIs:
if (typeof window !== 'undefined') { /* safe */ }
```

